Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Sr. Software Engineer position with Osmo Labs. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack development, data-intensive applications, and AI systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and developed back-end APIs using Python and Flask that translate natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across distributed systems. I architected data storage layers using PostgreSQL and Redis to support concurrent multi-agent orchestration, enabling scalable tool execution and reliable coordination across complex workflows. I also collaborated with the Product team to build proof of concepts for new AI-driven features, independently writing web UI components with React and TypeScript and back-end APIs with Python from scratch — directly mirroring the role's requirement to write exploratory tools and APIs independently and work across functional borders. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic data storage layer using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handles file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO — giving me direct hands-on experience with cloud platforms like GCP. I also developed back-end APIs and workflows using AWS Step Functions and Python to handle long-running data intensive import jobs, and contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot, SQL, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications. Together, these roles have prepared me to design and develop data storage layers, back-end APIs, and web UI, and to build and deploy data intensive applications as this role requires.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in machine learning, data-intensive computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I built data intensive applications for fashion design generation using PyTorch and CUDA on Pace University's HPC cluster, processing and training on large-scale image datasets. I developed exploratory tools and APIs for model inference using vLLM and Hugging Face, enabling secure and efficient model serving with Python and Flask. Beyond building the systems myself, I conducted workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly, demonstrating the technical communication and knowledge-sharing skills valued in collaborative engineering environments. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Osmo Labs.

I have always been passionate about applying machine learning and data science to solve real-world problems and improve human experiences, and I am deeply inspired by Osmo's mission to digitize the sense of smell to improve human health and happiness. The opportunity to combine proprietary molecular data, machine learning, and engineering to build Osmo's Olfactory Intelligence platform resonates strongly with my background in AI systems and data-intensive applications. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

